### Attribution of Datasets, Libraries, Frameworks, and External Resources

This project implements a lightweight task management application consisting of:

A Flask-based REST API

A simple in-memory data store

A browser-based interactive UI using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript

No third-party datasets, machine learning models, or external proprietary resources are used.

### Python Libraries

The backend makes use of standard open-source Python libraries, all under permissive licenses:

Flask — BSD-3 License

Flask-CORS — BSD License

Werkzeug — BSD License

Jinja2 — BSD License

ItsDangerous — BSD License

Click — BSD License

These libraries ship with permissive, open licenses that allow redistribution and modification.

### Frontend Libraries / Assets

This project uses:

Vanilla JavaScript (ES6) — No license restrictions

Custom CSS — Authored by the project creator

Bootstrap styles (optional) — MIT License (only minimal CSS class inspirations; no included Bootstrap files)

No external UI libraries (React, Vue, Tailwind, etc.) were used unless explicitly added by the user.

### Fonts

All fonts used are system defaults (e.g., Arial, sans-serif).
No external font files are bundled.

### Icons

Status badges (“Not Started”, “In Progress”, “Done”) use custom CSS inspired by Notion.
No icon packs or copyrighted assets are included or embedded.


### Images

The demo architecture diagram and any project images are:

Created by the project author

No third-party datasets, stock photos, or copyrighted media are bundled.

### Cloud Services

The cloud deployment uses:

Azure Web App for Containers

Azure Container Registry (ACR)

These are configuration components only.
No proprietary datasets or models are included as part of the software.

### No Proprietary Content


All dependencies are covered under open-source licenses compatible with MIT.